Review: This doesn’t happen for everyone but I recognized Cameron Diaz the instant she was on my screen.

Watched this in 4D at a little hole in the wall theater in crown heights. Historic performance from everyone, including but not limited to Josh Hutcherson, Tom Hanks as 4+ awful dudes, and of course The Hardy Boys, who made the film more than it could ever be. The rollercoaster simulation of the speeding train was so immersive I almost puked. A beautiful experience surrounded by pretty much all of my best friends.
Beginning was so awesome and then I completely lost the plot. Wanted more Robert Pattinson please.
Watched with my family and my dad said “I really liked but it’s definitely one where you have to let it cook…” we just taught him that

Nothing ever made has been anything like this.
